Object.create.description:
Object.create(proto, [propertiesObject]);
return a new object with the specified prototype object and properties.
A TypeError exception if the propertiesObject parameter is 'null' or a non-primitive-wrapper object.

body:
Object.defineProperty(${1:dest}, '${2:propertyName}', {
	get() {
		return ${3:value};
	},
	set(${4:newValue}) {
		${5:value} = ${4:newValue};
	},
	enumerable: ${6:false},
	configurable: ${7:false}
})

Object.defineProperties(${1:dest}, {
	${2:propertyName}: {
		configurable: ${3:false},
		enumerable: ${4:false}
		value: ${5:undefined},
		writable: ${6:false}
	},
	${7:propertyName}: {
		get() {
			return ${8:value};
		},
		set(${9:newValue}) {
			${10:value} = ${9:newValue};
		}
		enumerable: ${11:false},
		configurable: ${12:false}
	}
});

Object.seal.description:
Object.seal(obj);
seals an object, preventing new properties from being added to it and marking all existing properties as non-configurable. Values of present properties can still be changed as long as they are writable.
return the object being sealed.

*prototypeObj.isPrototypeOf.description:
prototypeObj.isPrototypeOf(object);
return a Boolean indicating whether the calling object lies in the prototype chain of the specified object.
thrown a TypeError is thrown if 'prototypeObj' is 'undefined' or 'null'.
